<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-570-334  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 570 334.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  June 11 1990 v7 n24 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Court strikes down Computer III edict. (Federal CommunicationsCommission's Third Computer Inquiry decision)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taff, Anita.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Federal Communications Committee's (FCC) Third ComputerInquiry decision has been overturned by a federal district court..andO;The court ruling calls into question whether the FCC can proceedwith Open Network Architecture (ONA).andP;  The three-judge panel ruledthat the FCC acted capriciously in 1986 when it replaced rulesrequiring regional Bell holding companies to offer enhancedservices through separate subsidiaries with accounting rules andother safeguards designed to prevent anticompetitive activities.andO;The ruling is seen as a major blow to the regional Bell telephonecompanies, who indicated that their being forced to offer enhancedservices through separate subsidiaries would result in severesocial costs for the public.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionLegal IssuesTelecommunicationsTelephone CompaniesGovernment RegulationCommunications Service SuppliersBell Regional Holding Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>